                <head>Comments</head>
                <p xml:id="CH1a0938-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-12a.84" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-04T22:38:03.059+09:00"> 與 is read as 興, cf. Mozi Jiaozhu p. 183, note 15.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:07:39.636+09:00">the peoples of distant states and diverse lands and the distinctions they made between matters of right and wrong or benefit and harm</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:09:00.331+09:00">could not be understood  by one or two alone. [adapted translation, TWH]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:21:56.561+09:00">Those who maintain solidarity with superiors and who do not form cliques with subordinates,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:24:23.333+09:00">they will be rewarded by superiors and praised by the inferiors. [adapted tr., TWH]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:39:58.816+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:40:03.705+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:40:14.709+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:40:28.135+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:40:38.148+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:40:45.485+09:00"> </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:40:53.182+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:41:01.072+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:41:11.315+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:41:16.735+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:41:26.575+09:00"> </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:41:38.451+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:41:47.97+09:00"/>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-2a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#twharbsmeier" modified="2020-06-05T19:44:50.883+09:00">that said: [TWH]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-13a.56" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-09T20:35:59.413+09:00">According to the 墨子校注 these lines should read: 奉承親戚</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-13a.57" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-09T20:36:22.578+09:00">提挈妻子家室</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-13a.58" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-09T20:37:05.302+09:00">而寄託之 (cf. Mozi jiaozhu, p. 185, n. 39).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-13a.59" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-09T20:38:19.891+09:00">有 read as 友 (cf. Mozi jiaozhu, p. 185, n. 40).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-14a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-15T18:37:00.046+09:00">According to the 墨子校注, ”君“ should read “之人” (cf. 墨子校注, p. 187, n. 59).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-14a.55" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-15T18:37:00.866+09:00">“此” is missing in this line (cf. 墨子校注, p. 187, n. 60).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-15a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-16T21:07:40.761+09:00">“獨“ should read “猶” (cf. 墨子校注, p. 187, n. 64).</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-15a.87" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-30T20:35:17.5+09:00">底 read as 砥 (cf. 墨子校注, p. 193-94, </seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_004-15a.91" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-06-30T20:57:03.071+09:00">正 read as 政.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0938_CHANT_003-21a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#wilke" modified="2020-07-21T21:29:13.411+09:00">賞 is to be read as 嘗. 嘗使家君 and 試用家君 are tautological. See 墨子校注, p. 146, note 42.</seg>
                </p>
